    </equation><para id="import-auto-id2670890">Substituting the values of torque and moment of inertia into the expression for <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>α</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>, we obtain</para>
    <equation id="eip-877"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>α</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mtext>64</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>0 N</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">⋅</m:mo><m:mtext>m</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>4.352 kg</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">⋅</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>m</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mtext>14.7</m:mtext><m:mfrac><m:mtext>rad</m:mtext><m:msup><m:mtext>s</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></equation><para id="import-auto-id3400808">Now, substitute this value and the given value for <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> into the above expression for <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>ω</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>:</para>
    <equation id="eip-116"><m:math>
        
          <m:mrow>

              <m:mrow>
