    <exercise id="fs-id2402678" type="problems-exercises">
      <problem id="fs-id3255931">
      <para id="import-auto-id2963400">This problem considers energy and work aspects of <link document="m42179" target-id="fs-id1468671"/>—use data from that example as needed. (a) Calculate the rotational kinetic energy in the merry-go-round plus child when they have an angular velocity of 20.0 rpm. (b) Using energy considerations, find the number of revolutions the father will have to push to achieve this angular velocity starting from rest. (c) Again, using energy considerations, calculate the force the father must exert to stop the merry-go-round in two revolutions</para></problem>
